Package: waffle-nbd
Version: @VERSION@
Architecture: @ARCH@
Maintainer: Gianluca Renzi <gianlucarenzi@eurek.it>
Depends: nbd-client, kmod, util-linux
Recommends: libnotify-bin, xdg-utils
Description: NBD server for DrawBridge/Waffle floppy reader
 waffle-nbd exposes a DrawBridge or Waffle V2 floppy disk as a Linux
 Network Block Device (/dev/nbd0), mountable with standard kernel drivers
 (affs for Amiga OFS/FFS, vfat for DOS FAT).
 .
 Includes udev rules for automatic hot-plug detection and mounting, a
 polkit rule that allows active local users to unmount /dev/nbd* without
 password, and a systemd-run based handler for the full plug-in lifecycle.
 .
 Supports FTDI FT230X (Waffle V2, VID:PID 0403:6015) and FT232RL
 (classic DrawBridge, 0403:6001).
